.TH "kernfs_create_root" 9 "kernfs_create_root" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kernfs_create_root \- create a new kernfs hierarchy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct kernfs_root *" kernfs_create_root
.BI "(struct kernfs_syscall_ops *scops "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ","
.BI "void *priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "scops" 12
optional syscall operations for the hierarchy
.IP "flags" 12
KERNFS_ROOT_* flags
.IP "priv" 12
opaque data associated with the new directory
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the root of the new hierarchy on success, \fBERR_PTR\fP value on
failure.
